[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has a low-range 1NT opener; a balanced hand with 15 points.

NORTH has 16 points; he figures the partnership holds either 31, 32 or 33. 
Obviously he wants to at least reach game, but if SOUTH holds 17 points he wants to reach slam.

NORTH bids 4NT. Since this is more than game it should be clear to SOUTH that he is asking 
her to bid 6NT if she is at the top of her range. It is clear to SOUTH, but with just 15 points she passes.}

